    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT47-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">irā vantoḻukuṅ kālai muṉṉilaip puṟamoḻiyāka nilāviṟku uraippāḷākat tōḻi uraittatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Declared to the confidante as if declared to the moonlight to scold the addressee in the time that was long as the night had come.</p>
          </div>



        <div xml:id="KT47">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                karuṅkāl vēṅkai vīyuku tuṟuka</l>
<l>                lirumpulik kuruḷaiyiṟ ṟōṉṟuṅ kāṭṭiṭai</l>
<l>                yelli varunar kaḷaviṟku</l>
<l>                nallai yallai neṭuveṇ ṇilavē.</l>

             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
             <l rend="indent">For the tryst with the one who comes at night</l>
             <l rend="indent">when a thick stone strewn with blossoms</l>
             <l rend="indent4">of the black-trunked Vēṅkai</l>
             <l rend="indent">appears like a big tiger cub, in the middle of the wilderness,</l>
             <l>you are no good<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">nallai yallai</term> cf. KT 102.4 <term xml:lang="ta">cāṉṟōr allar</term>.</note>, long white moonlight!</l>
                </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
